  "issue_number": 88,
  "issue_title": "feature: add observe_screen_context tool",
  "issue_body": "Parent: #75\n\n## Problem\n\nTouchPilot exposes `observe_screen` as a raw Accessibility tree dump, but Milestone 3 added structured `ScreenContext` for local screen understanding.\n\nAgents and debug tooling need a structured observation tool that returns the normalized context directly.\n\n## Proposed behavior\n\nAdd an `observe_screen_context` Android tool that returns a redacted serialized `ScreenContext`.\n\nThe output should include:\n\n- app/package/window metadata,\n- visible nodes,\n- roles,\n- bounds,\n- click/input/scroll flags,\n- sensitive text redacted or marked safely.\n\n## User workflow\n\nThe local agent can inspect structured screen context before choosing reliable tool actions.\n\n## Local-first impact\n\nStructured local context is the bridge between Milestone 3 understanding and Milestone 4 reliable control.\n\n## Safety and security considerations\n\n`ScreenContext` can contain sensitive visible text. Output must use display-safe/redacted text by default and avoid leaking raw sensitive values in logs or traces.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Add `observe_screen_context` to the Android tool catalog.\n- [ ] Serialize `ScreenContext` in a stable JSON shape.\n- [ ] Redact sensitive text by default.\n- [ ] Keep `observe_screen` available for raw debug compatibility.\n- [ ] Add tests for serialization, redaction, and empty context.\n- [ ] Document when agents should prefer structured context over raw dumps.\n\n## Alternatives considered\n\nOnly keep `observe_screen`. Rejected because raw text dumps are harder to rank, verify, and evolve safely.\n",
  "merged_at": "2026-06-01T19:23:43.000Z",
